# Database Rules

- Use Prisma Client for all database operations.
- Run `npx prisma db push` after schema changes.
- Use `include` for relations, avoid N+1 queries.

## Models

### Account

Fields: id, userId, type, provider, providerAccountId, refresh_token, access_token, expires_at, token_type, scope, id_token, session_state
Relations: user

### Session

Fields: id, sessionToken, userId, expires
Relations: user

### VerificationToken

Fields: identifier, token, expires

### User

Fields: id, name, email, emailVerified, image, githubId, stripeCustomerId, createdAt, updatedAt
Relations: plan, accounts, sessions, repositories, customRules

### Repository

Fields: id, userId, githubRepoId, name, fullName, defaultBranch, private, language, description, scanRoot, actionInstalled, lastScanAt, createdAt, updatedAt
Relations: user, scans, searchChunks

### Scan

Fields: id, repositoryId, results, fileCount, lineCount, componentCount, hookCount, apiRouteCount, modelCount, tokenEstimate, error, duration, commitSha, createdAt, updatedAt
Relations: status, repository, generatedFiles, searchChunks

### GeneratedFile

Fields: id, scanId, fileName, content, tokenCount, createdAt
Relations: format, scan

### CustomRule

Fields: id, userId, name, description, rule, enabled, createdAt, updatedAt
Relations: scope, user

### SearchChunk

Fields: id, repositoryId, scanId, sectionHeading, sectionType, content, chunkIndex, tokenCount, createdAt
Relations: searchVector, repository, scan
